title: Grateful Dead Live at Autzen Stadium, U. of Oregon on 1990-06-23
description: Feel Like A Stranger-> West L.A. Fadeaway, Me & My Uncle, Cumberland Blues, Far From Me, They Love Each Other, Cassidy, Tennessee Jed, Promised Land Eyes Of The World, Looks Like Rain-> Crazy Fingers-> Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> I Need A Miracle-> Morning Dew, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Thank You! Wow! I can't believe I am the first to review this show. I must say thank you to the taper who taped this show. A professional indeed. On par with the oade brothers! So Thanks!

A great one The first set is high energy and chaotic.  Track  one is tuning and eqipment fixes.  Blasts  of sound from the p.a.  are highly unpleasant.  Avoid it.

As for the energy; it's nuts.  Totally nuts.  Phil has a tone that cuts through  so loud and bouncey that the music perhaps suffers a little.  Nonetheless, very very fun.

Great performances of Cumberland, Cassidy, They  Love each Other and more.

Secoond set is where it's at.  Very loose feeling throughout, well paced,  relaxed, then roaring.  Check out the  lyrical eyes, the thunder machine on Looks Like Rain, the trippy jam in playin', the roaring climax to  Uncle John's, the  unusually trippy journey in  drums (this one's extremely fun, beginning from  a few minutes in).

And post space is a bang.  The Wheel is well paced, a great jam follows Miracle  (rages  for a few), and my favorite Dew.  This dew is so great that I've practically memorized every note.  Start to finish, jolting into the stops and the breaks, yet smooth and sailing through the changes.  The closing solo is a pure, unadulterated cry from the heart of of Jerry garcia.  One of my favorite things he ever played.

Just get it.  The sound is likewise spectacular.  A great recording.

Great sounding AUD Sound is as good as it gets with AUDs - and download worthy even for SBD-ers. 

Track list is off tho - track named Feel Like a Stranger is pre-show tuning up and noise. West LA is actually Stanger, and so on

then there's a brief pre-2nd set tuning that is also mis-named as Looks Like Rain, so then it's off by two.

Bear with it tho... great sounding AUD and nice  spirited vintage '90 show.
